ty\n, where you can connect with people who understand ADHD. Celebrate wins and help each other to stay motivated and on track.\nproductivity strategy that involves doing a task in the presence of another person\nIt’s a well-established and proven\nADHD productivity technique\nthat can be a game-changer for managing ADHD symptoms, promoting concentration, and boosting task completion.\nget started, stay focused, and ultimately accomplish your tasks\nmore productive, efficient and energised\ninattentive ADHD type\n, virtual body doubling provides a\nhyperactive ADHD\nanchor that makes it much easier to stay focused on a task\n. The physical cue provides a subtle\nVirtual body doubling ADHD sessions offer many advantages, including\n- all crucial for managing ADHD.\nADHD accountability buddy\npresence of others can improve our performance on tasks\nfocus, making it easier to start and stay on task\nfocused and motivated and less likely to be distracted\nIt might sound oddly simple, but this method has a profound impact for anyone with ADHD.\nWhy is it so effective for ADHD?\nBody doubling is a tried and tested productivity strategy that\noriginated in the ADHD community about 30 years ago.\nIt boosts motivation, focus and task completion for people with ADHD by leveraging the power of\nshared focus, social facilitation, and gentle social accountability.\n, keeping you tethered to the task at hand, nudging you away from procrastination and getting distracted. This passive form of accountability\nenhances focus, wards off procrastination, and increases task completion\nsense of calm and focus\n, tempering the tumultuous tides of ADHD.\n. The reduced distractions and enhanced task completion add an element of stability to the often chaotic world of ADHD.\nimprove positive behaviours by 50%\nduring a body doubling session promotes focus on a single activity and can\nimprove productivity by up to 40%","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false